wwpLeosDhcpClientMIB.name: wwpLeosDhcpClientMIB

revisions.description: Add new tables to support DHCP relay agent functionality. Range of wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpAddr limited to 1..15.

wwpLeosDhcpClientMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosDhcpClientMIB.description: The MIB module to manage DHCP client on WWP LEOS products.

wwpLeosDhcpIfName.name: wwpLeosDhcpIfName
wwpLeosDhcpIfName.description: The ifDesc associated with the DHCP client. it can be set to 'remote' or 'local'

wwpLeosDhcpStatus.name: wwpLeosDhcpStatus
wwpLeosDhcpStatus.description: Setting this object to 'enable' will enable the DHCP client on this interface.

wwpLeosDhcpState.name: wwpLeosDhcpState
wwpLeosDhcpState.description: The current state of the DHCP client on this interface as per RFC2131.

wwpLeosDhcpLeaseOffered.name: wwpLeosDhcpLeaseOffered
wwpLeosDhcpLeaseOffered.description: The lease time authorized by the server.

wwpLeosDhcpLeaseRemaining.name: wwpLeosDhcpLeaseRemaining
wwpLeosDhcpLeaseRemaining.description: The time remaining for the lease to expire.

wwpLeosDhcpDiscoveryMsgInterval.name: wwpLeosDhcpDiscoveryMsgInterval
wwpLeosDhcpDiscoveryMsgInterval.description: The time interval for discovery messages issued before the client receives the first reply.

wwpLeosDhcpRenewalTime.name: wwpLeosDhcpRenewalTime
wwpLeosDhcpRenewalTime.description: The number of seconds before the client begins to renew its address lease with the DHCP server. This time is a function typically 50% of the full configured duration (or lease time) for a client lease. Referred to as T1 in RFC2131.

wwpLeosDhcpRebindingTime.name: wwpLeosDhcpRebindingTime
wwpLeosDhcpRebindingTime.description: The number of seconds before the client enters the rebinding state if it has not renewed its current address lease with the DHCP server. This time is a function (typically, 87.5%) of the full configured duration (or lease time) for a client lease. Referred to as T2 in RFC2131.

wwpLeosDhcpServerAddress.name: wwpLeosDhcpServerAddress
wwpLeosDhcpServerAddress.description: The IP address that identifies the DHCP server.

wwpLeosDhcpRenewLease.name: wwpLeosDhcpRenewLease
wwpLeosDhcpRenewLease.description: Setting this object to true will force the DHCP client to renew its lease.

wwpLeosDhcpReleaseLease.name: wwpLeosDhcpReleaseLease
wwpLeosDhcpReleaseLease.description: Setting this object to true will force the DHCP client to release its lease, if the client DHCP is in the bound state

wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionTable
wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionTable.description: List of options supported by the DHCP client.

wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionEntry
wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionEntry.description: An entry containing list of options supported by DHCP client.

wwpLeosDhcpOptionCodeIndex.name: wwpLeosDhcpOptionCodeIndex
wwpLeosDhcpOptionCodeIndex.description: Specifies the index used for this entry.

wwpLeosDhcpOptionDesc.name: wwpLeosDhcpOptionDesc
wwpLeosDhcpOptionDesc.description: Specifies the description for the given DHCP option code.

wwpLeosDhcpOptionCode.name: wwpLeosDhcpOptionCode
wwpLeosDhcpOptionCode.description: Specifies the option code specified by RFC specification.

wwpLeosDhcpOptionState.name: wwpLeosDhcpOptionState
wwpLeosDhcpOptionState.description: Specifies if the given option is enabled/disabled.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCircuitId.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCircuitId
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCircuitId.description: Specifies what circuit ID should be used by DHCP relay agent.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentRemoteId.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentRemoteId
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentRemoteId.description: This object specifies what remote agent ID is used by DHCP relay agent. it can be set to macAddress or hostName.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2State.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2State
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2State.description: Specifies the global state of DHCP L2 relay agent.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3State.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3State
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3State.description: Specifies the global state of DHCP L3 relay agent.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StateTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StateTable
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StateTable.description: Tables allows changing configuration of DHCP relay agent functionality for each wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StateEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StateEntry
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StateEntry.description: Entry in the table to configure DHCP relay agent functionality.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan.description: This mib object specifies the VLAN on which DHCP relay agent is configured.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2AdminState.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2AdminState
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2AdminState.description: This object allows to disable or enable DHCP relay agent functionality on the given VLAN specified by wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2OperState.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2OperState
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2OperState.description: This object shows the operational status of the DHCP relay agent on given VLAN.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsClear.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsClear
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsClear.description: This mib object when set to 'true' clears DHCP relay agent stats for given VLAN.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2RowStatus.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2RowStatus
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2RowStatus.description: Set this MIB object to 'Destroy' to terminate DHCP L2 Relaying on the VLAN specified by wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan. Set this MIB object to 'CreateAndGo' to enable DHCP L2 Relaying on the VLAN specified by wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3StateTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3StateTable
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3StateTable.description: Tables allows changing configuration of DHCP relay agent functionality for each wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3StateEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3StateEntry
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3StateEntry.description: Entry in the table to configure DHCP relay agent functionality.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex.description: This mib object specifies the value of the mib object wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentIndexType. So if wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentIndexType = interface then this object represents the interface index. if it is set to VLAN then this object represents the VLAN id and so on.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3AdminState.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3AdminState
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3AdminState.description: This object allows to disable or enable DHCP relay agent functionality for each wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentIndexType.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3OperState.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3OperState
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3OperState.description: This object shows the operational status of the DHCP relay agent on the given interface.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3RowStatus.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3RowStatus
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL3RowStatus.description: Set this MIB object to 'Destroy' to terminate DHCP L3 Relaying on the VLAN specified by wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex. Set this MIB object to 'CreateAndGo' to enable DHCP L3 Relaying on the VLAN specified by wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpTable
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpTable.description: This table can be used to add the trusted IP addresses or host names on each interface.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpEntry
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents the trusted DHCP server IP address on each interface.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpIndex.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpIndex
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpIndex.description: This mib object is used as an index in the table and represents the unique index of the IP address for a given wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIndex.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpAddr.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpAddr
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpAddr.description: This mib object is used to specify the IP address of the DHCP server which is trusted IP address. This object cannot be modified once entry is created with some IP.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpRowStatu.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpRowStatus
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentInterfaceIpRowStatu.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table set this object to 'destroy'.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustTable
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustTable.description: This table can be used to specify what slot / ports and vlans DHCP relay agent can trust.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustEntry
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustEntry.description: Each entry in this table can be used to specify the slot / port and VLAN to be trusted.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentPort.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentPort
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentPort.description: This mib object is used as index in the table and is used to specify the port.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustMode.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustMode
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentTrustMode.description: This mib object can be used to set the port as client trusted, server trusted or not trusted.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsTable
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsTable.description: Tables to display L2 statistics for each wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentVlan.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsEntry
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2StatsEntry.description: Entry in the table to display l2 stats.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2IpSecHeaders.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2IpSecHeaders
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2IpSecHeaders.description: This MIB object specifies the number of packets that include IP Sec Headers.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82Added.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82Added
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82Added.description: This MIB object specifies the number of packets that have had option 82 added.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82Removed.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82Removed
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82Removed.description: This MIB object specifies the number of packets that have had option 82 removed.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2UntrustedClientPo.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2UntrustedClientPortPktsRx
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2UntrustedClientPo.description: This MIB object specifies the number of packets received on untrusted client ports.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2UntrustedServerPo.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2UntrustedServerPortPktsRx
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2UntrustedServerPo.description: This MIB object specifies the number of packets received from untrusted server ports.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2SpoofedDhcpPkts.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2SpoofedDhcpPkts
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2SpoofedDhcpPkts.description: This MIB object specifies the number of spoofed DHCP packets.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82ExceedMTU.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82ExceedMTU
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2Option82ExceedMTU.description: This MIB object specifies the number of packets with DHCP option 82 that exceed option 82.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2NoTrustedServerPk.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2NoTrustedServerPktDrop
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2NoTrustedServerPk.description: This MIB object specifies the number of DHCP packets dropped because there are no server trusted ports configured.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2NoTrustedClientPk.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2NoTrustedClientPktDrop
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentL2NoTrustedClientPk.description: This MIB object specifies the number of DHCP packets dropped because there are no client trusted ports configured.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringTable.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringTable
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringTable.description: This table can be used to specify cid strings for slot / ports and vlans dhcp relay agent can specify in Option 82 CID information.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringEntry.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringEntry
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringEntry.description: Each entry in this table can be used to specify a cid string for slot / port and vlan combinations.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringPort.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringPort
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringPort.description: This mib object is used as index in the table and is used to specify the port.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidString.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidString
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidString.description: This mib object can be used to set the cid string for the port.

wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringRowStatus.name: wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringRowStatus
wwpLeosDhcpRelayAgentCidStringRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table set this object to 'createAndGo'. To delete a row in this table set this object to 'destroy'.

wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionDisabledNotificat.name: wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionDisabledNotification
wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionDisabledNotificat.description: A wwpLeosDhcpClientOptionDisabledNotification is sent whenever device receives DHCP option which is disabled on the device.
